<p id="notice"><%= notice %></p>


<div class="col-lg-8 col-lg-offset-2">
  <h1>Add Containers</h1>
  <p>Crapper Keeper works backwards - start with the biggest container (your house, apartment, building, etc.)
and keep working down into the container your item will be stored in. </p>
  <br>
  <p>An example: Barn Owl House -- Foyer -- Closet -- Pink Canvas Bag </p>
  <br>
  <p>After you add containers add some <strong>Items</strong> inside the container.</p>
  <p>You can add <strong>Items</strong> by clicking on the <strong>Show</strong> button of the container
  it will go in followed by clicking <strong>Add Items</strong></p>
  <br>
</div>
<br>



<div class="col-lg-8 col-lg-offset-2">

  <% unless Container.exists? %>
      <p>No containers to display!  Click the button to add a new container!</p>
  <% end %>

  <table class="table">
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Name</th>
        <th>Description</th>
        <th>Parent</th>
        <th colspan="3"></th>
      </tr>
    </thead>

    <tbody>
      <% @containers.each do |container| %>
        <tr>
          <td><%= container.name %></td>
          <td><%= container.description %></td>
          <td><%= container.parent.try!(:name) %></td>
          <td><%= link_to 'Show', container, class: "btn btn-info btn-sm" %></td>
          <td><%= link_to 'Edit', edit_container_path(container), class: "btn btn-info btn-sm" %></td>
          <td><%= link_to 'Destroy', container, method: :delete, data: { confirm: 'Are you sure?' }, class: "btn btn-info btn-sm" %></td>
        </tr>
      <% end %>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</div>

<br>

<div class="col-lg-8 col-lg-offset-2">
  <%= link_to 'Add A New Container!', new_container_path, class: "btn btn-success btn-lg" %>
</div>